arts.ttl: Ange Postecoglou matches key Jose Mourinho feat that not even Antonio Conte could emulate after Tottenham's 2-1 Europa League win
arts.sum: Postecoglou's team won 2-1 away to Ferencvaros to maintain their winning start to their Europa League campaign.

Ange was asked a number of questions on the four teenagers who started against Ferencvaros - debutant Will Lankshear, Mikey Moore, making his first start, Lucas Bergvall and Archie Gray... We needed to defend and defend well, we played some good football and created some good chances, maybe could have had a couple more and most importantly we won an away European tie which I think is a credit to the lads."

arts.ttl: Ange Postecoglou on Mikey Moore: 'Lamine Yamal isn't doing it in the Premier League'
arts.sum: Ange Postecoglou waxes lyrical about Tottenham Hotspur wonderkid Mikey Moore following the Lilywhites' 2-1 win over Ferencvaros in the Europa League.

arts.ttl: Tottenham boss hails his young guns but is not a fan of ‘Ange’s Angels’ tag
arts.sum: Mikey Moore was labelled as ‘special’ by Ange Postecoglou after he was given his full debut in Budapest.

arts.ttl: Joe Cole hails Tottenham youngster after impressive Europa League display as Chelsea icon explains why the 17-year-old 'star' will have Son Heung-min looking over his shoulder
arts.sum: The 17-year-old gave a very good account of himself on his first senior start as Tottenham ran out 2-1 winners.

arts.ttl: Postecoglou admits he never understood why Spurs star was criticised
arts.sum: Tottenham Hotspur registered an important win in the Europa League tonight, and after the game, Ange Postecoglou had yet more praise for one of his... The post Postecoglou admits he never understood why Spurs star was criticised appeared first on Spurs Web.

arts.ttl: Ferencvaros 1-2 Tottenham: Highlights, man of the match, stats as Spurs continue winning run
arts.sum: Tottenham Hotspur continue their winning run with a 2-1 success over Ferencvaros in the Europa League on Thursday night.

arts.ttl: UEFA deny Spurs request, Moore and things spotted in Ferencvaros vs Tottenham
arts.sum: Starting with Will Lankshear leading the line and Mikey Moore and Timo Werner either side of him in attack, the Spurs striker had a good chance inside the first ten minutes but he could only head the German's cross over from close range . Fresh from last Sunday's 3-0 win against Manchester United at Old Trafford, Ange Postecoglou made seven changes to his Spurs team in order to give those on the periphery of the starting XI some much-needed pitch time.

arts.ttl: Tottenham make it two from two in Europa League with hard-fought win in Budapest
arts.sum: A Spurs team which included four teenagers made it five victories in a row in all competitions.

arts.ttl: Tottenham player ratings vs Ferencvaros: Mikey Moore shines as Timo Werner struggles
arts.sum: The teenager, on his first start, outshone his experienced fellow forward
